post_text: Noteworthy items for EJSS
shared_text:
East Jackson Secondary School
August 24 at 10:15 PM ·

Good evening Trojan Families,

A few major items for EJSS students as we near the start of school.

-Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday are half days and will end at 12PM

- As students arrive to school on Wednesday they will need to check in at their grade level table to receive their schedule- the tables will be located in front of the building. After check in they will go to their locker, and then 1st hour for breakfast.

-Students attending face to face classes need to bring anything they owe the school from the spring (including computers). Students will be getting newly assigned computers during 1st hour.

-Students starting school online will need to stop into the office to pick up their computers. You may do that Wednesday through Friday, 7:30-2:30. Please bring anything your child owes the school from the spring.

If you have questions please call the school at 517-764-1700.

EJSS dismissed at 12:00 pm each day
EJE dismissed at 1:00 pm each day

Normal schedule will return on Monday, August 31:
EJSS dismissal at 2:13 pm
EJE dismissal at 3:13 pm

Elementary Families:
On Monday, Superintendent Doerr provided information regarding the 6 different phases our EJ school community could be in at any given time. We currently are in Phase 4, which includes an in-person school option for families. (You can see his letter on the East Jackon Schools website) Below you will find a suggested school supply list broken down by grade levels. Please contact Mrs. Hager, Principal at becky.hager@eastjacksonschools.org with any questions you may have. **Of special note more details will be provided soon in regards to the EJCS Reopening Plan.

post_text:
The EJSS middle school staff would like to take a moment to recognize its All Honors Recipients and Nominees for the 2020 school year. All Honors, dating back nearly 50 years, is presented to two 8th grade students who have exhibited outstanding scholarship, citizenship, and leadership over the two years attending middle school at EJSS.

This year's All Honors Recipients are Jordan Wineland and Gavin Zegarlowicz. Their names will be added to the office plaque of past winners.

Also nominated to receive this honor were Kaitlyn Ballew, Kylie Bates, Brock Davidson, Aaliyah Kelly, Joseph Murray, Colton Raffensberger, Ella Scott, and Kayla Winget.

Congratulations goes to each of these students, and their families, for their outstanding effort and character over the past two years.

Elementary Families:

Please mark your calendars for pick up of items that were in your child’s locker/desk for either Tuesday, May 26th from 9-2, Wednesday, May 27th from 12-6, and Thursday, May 28th from 9-2. With the governor's orders extended to the end of the month, having families come in to clean out these items will not give us enough time to close down the building and for teachers to complete the end of the year activities. Teachers will be checking desks and lockers for school items and staff will be bagging up your child’s items for you. The procedure will be to drive up to the front doors during the pickup times and let us know your child’s name and we will get the items and bring them to your car. Please email Mrs. Hager becky.hager@eastjacksonschools.org or Mrs. Blackledge amy.blackledge@eastjacksonschools.org if you have any questions.

Attention East Jackson Secondary Students:

I hope all of you are laying low and staying safe! When you have time please make sure you check your email, Google Classroom, Schoology, etc... Our teachers have provided some great educational resources that can help you sharpen your skills while you are not in school. More importantly, our teachers wanted to reach out to all of you and make sure you are doing ok. Please do not hesitate to contact any of us if you have any questions and we all look forward to seeing you...eventually!

Sincerely,

Mr. Cook

post_text:
In case you have not already heard, Gov. Whitmer has ordered the closure of all K-12 school buildings during the period of March 16-April 5.

EJ Schools will remain open on Friday, March 13 in order for staff to prepare for the unplanned recess period. Elementary field trips will go on as scheduled.

There are some implications regarding this closure that are unresolved at this time. The most important of these are Food insecurity for many EJ students. I will continue to advocate for the needs of families and staff on behalf of our district in all of these challenges that we will face together.

Please continue to watch for important updates for EJ staff and families through:
A. The district website: eastjacksonschools.org
B. The district Facebook page
C. District all-calls through our call system
D. Staff email

column1: The Snowfest dances will take place on Saturday

- The Middle School dance will begin at 5pm (students should not arrive before 4:45 pm) and conclude at 7 pm. Please make sure all rides are here by 7:15! This dance is for EJSS Middle school students only. No visitors

- The High School dance begins at 7:30 pm and concludes at 10 pm. High school students wishing to bring a non-EJSS guests must have the necessary form completed and in Mr. Cook’s possession by the end of the school day Friday.
- The cost of each dance is $5. Concessions will be available for purchases.

link:
The Snowfest Court Ceremony will take place this Friday, January 31st, immediately following the conclusion of the JV boys basketball game (approximately 6:45.)

The Snowfest dances will take place on Saturday, February 1st.

- The Middle School dance will begin at 5pm (students should not arrive before 4:45 pm) and conclude at 7 pm. Please make sure all rides are here by 7:15! This dance is for EJSS Middle school students only. No visitors, siblings, etc..

- The High School dance begins at 7:30 pm and concludes at 10 pm. High school students wishing to bring a non-EJSS guests must have the necessary form completed and in Mr. Cook’s possession by the end of the school day Friday.

- The cost of each dance is $5. Concessions will be available for purchases.

Thank You,

Mr. Smith

EJE girls in grades 3-5. Registration for Girls on the Run is NOW Open! The earlier you register, the easier it is to get financial help! If your girl is interested in participating, and you can't afford the high cost, there are scholarship options available - you have to register and select that you need financial assistance. They will then lower your cost significantly and payments can be made over time (select the option to pay by check).
https://www.girlsontherunsemi.org/program-registration

Practices are Monday and Wednesday after school until 5:30 and begin March 9th!

link:
Each year, East Jackson hosts a basketball game to honor those in our community that are fighting or have lost their fight with cancer. This year, there are 2 games--Girls on Feb. 6 & Boys on Feb. 7.

You can help support our efforts by buying a Purple-Out Shirt and joining us at this event. Pre-orders for the Purple-Out T-shirt are due this coming Friday, January 10. You can turn your orders into either the high school or elementary office. Pre-ordered shirts can be picked up at the game on Feb. 6/7.

Thank you for supporting this wonderful cause and we hope to see you there!
